Multiple variables should not be declared on the same line
Why is this an issue? Declaring multiple variables on one line is difficult to read. 
### Noncompliant
class MyClass {

  private int a, b;

  public void method(){
    int c; int d;
  }
}
### Compliant
class MyClass {

  private int a;
  private int b;

  public void method(){
    int c;
    int d;
  }
}
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
### Compliant
